oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Certificate of service for Fireman First Class Guy E. Housholder, U.S.N.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Guy E. Housholder of Knoxville enlisted at age 18 and served on the minelayer U.S.S. Housatonic as a Fireman 2nd Class. This certificate identifies him as a Fireman first class who served with Mine Squadron One in the North Sea during World War I. Housholder was honorably discharged as an Engineman 2nd Class on August 32, 1919. After the war, he worked as a machinist for the railroad, and died in 1961.
